President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Oklahoma and authorized federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts following severe storms, tornadoes, and straight-line winds on April 14, 2011. The declaration makes federal funding available to affected individuals in Atoka County, including grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid in recovery. Federal funding is also available for hazard mitigation measures statewide. William J. Doran III has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional counties may be designated for assistance once damage assessments are completed. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. FEMA can be contacted for further information.